# WindowDebugPanelSystem

## Purpose
Renders an ImGui "Window" panel with a preset-resolution dropdown (1280x720, 1600x900, 1920x1080), a
Windowed/Fullscreen radio, and an Apply button. The current live resolution + mode (from
`WindowConfigSingletonComponent`) is shown and seeds the panel selection on first use. On Apply it emits
a `SetWindowResolutionRequestOneFrameComponent` carrying the chosen resolution + mode so the engine
`WindowConfigSystem` applies it to the live window and persists it to the savedata config. Returns early
when the window-config singleton is absent or when no ImGui context exists (the Testing build pushes no
ImGui layer).

The in-progress panel selection (chosen preset + mode) is held in `WindowPanelSelectionSingletonComponent`,
owned by this system and seeded once from the live window config — mirroring how `DebugPanelSystem` keeps
its controls in a singleton. It is owned by the user between frames until Apply.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| WindowConfigSingletonComponent | read | Shows the current resolution/mode and seeds the panel selection |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| WindowPanelSelectionSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | The panel's pending preset + mode; created once seeded from the live config, then updated in place |
| SetWindowResolutionRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted when Apply is pressed |
